Description: Rectangular fragment of sandstone relief bearing Greek dedication to Diocletian and Constantius I (originally also Maximian and Galerius).
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Egypt, said to be from Philae
Curator's comments: Bernand, É. , Les inscriptions grecques de Philae II (Paris 1969), no. 185 (p. 209-12), pl. 93.
Bibliographic references: Inscription / The Collection of Ancient Greek Inscriptions in the British Museum (1078)
